items.description:
This model was trained on a bunch of faces that don't fully comply with the common beauty standards. There's more to the world than just beautiful people, so here is a model that lets you create "girl next door" faces with slight imperfections.

As base checkpoint I used epicrealism_newCentury because for my taste it generates the best natural skin textures. Weights around 0.5 should be a good start. Higher values lead into "butterface" territory.

The model is NSFW friendly and should also work with other photorealstic checkpoints but you might need to tweak the parameters a bit.

Prompts for the example pictures are deliberately minimalist, so you can see what what the model can do out of the box.

Please note that the model was only trained on pictures of white women. I might add other ethnicities in the future if I find the time.

For inpainting use the same model but converted it to an inpaint version with the checkpoint merger of webui. Inpainting this LoRA without an inpainting model will be hard.

Euler a: Smoother images

Use 512x768 for image size and upscale later.

CFG scale depends on the tags you are using. Anywhere in the range from 2 to 6 should work. Lower values are better.

The close up sample images are created by txt2img without editing. The full body images are completely inpainted from real images.

Mixing this Lora with Lilly works realy good.

Upscaling

For best results I am using ControlNet with type tile + Ultimate SD upscale to keep the image stable without adding ghost pussy all over the place. Upscale 2-3x works most of the time.

The Winchester Repeating Arms Company had been looking into introducing a shotgun to their catalogue offerings in the 1880s. The choice to design a shotgun rather than a handgun is due in part to an agreement made between Colt and Winchester. In order to preserve both company's profits and not divide the market, Colt agreed not to produce a rifle (Winchester's primary market), while Winchester agreed to not produce a revolver (Colt's primary market). And so in order to supplement Winchester's rifle sales, the legendary firearms designer and long-time partner of Winchester John Browning was tasked to design a new shotgun for the company. Browning had actually already been in the process of designing a shotgun, and suggested the use of a pump action mechanism for cycling the action. However, Winchester's vice-president at the time, T.G. Bennett, said that Winchester was known more as a "lever-action gun company", and as such the new shotgun should also be a lever-action weapon to preserve brand recognition. Browning responded by designing a breech-loading, lever-action shotgun, which Winchester adopted and sold as the Model 1887.

The MAIN purpose of this LORA is to create character arts in an specific style (cowboy, cowgirl and related) but without the needs of specify the clothing (the style will drag to it) and at the same time, being able to specify if the user wants, so it will work both sides. It will act as Lazy LORA (due to how was trained) and it can act as detail LORA the moment you start long-prompting (where you can say what items in the wearing, etc.).

It can create interiors, landscapes and exteriors* (I will explain later this since some models are better for this purpose).

- Token is: w3st.

How to use this?
******************
- LORA's strenght recommended: 0.7-1.1 (you can work with 1 with no problems but for advanced prompting or complex things maybe 0.9 is a more safe value).

Note: In the case you don't know you can decide to NOT use the token when playing with values and still it's going to work (however I'd recommend to use it in normal circumstances).

- For characters if you want to use the Lazy Lora tech. "w3st male/female portrait/side portrait" and that should be all. If you want to be more specific with places, outfits, etc. I suggest you to drop the LORA to values between 0.8-0.9 and if you find some problems with specific clothing, 0.7.


- For landscapes/interiors/exteriors I suggest you use Colorful model (I used 3.0), and Dreamshaper (I used 3.32 ClipFix). Others can work but didnt test every single one.

- In terms of general aesthetics if you want some cool anime generations Ghostmix and DarkSushiMix are your friends. If you want overall Colorful v3.0 works very good (same as Dreamshaper or Faetastic).


- If you're thinking on guns and weapons, use ControlNet. AI itself can't get that in an easy way (probably other LORA's for that task can help).

This is LORA is good for:

- Character designing, portraiture. in a range of semi realistic-anime-illustration and *probably realistic with RV2.0*

- Mixing with other character LORA's.

- Structures, landscapes, interiors, exteriors.

- Popular people stylish-adaptation

This LORA is NOT designed for:

- Extremely complex landscaping/architecture

- Shotgun, gun, weapons holding gens. without ControlNet

Last but not least I will be throwing a Patreon version with almost the same but with some enhancements (although I really think this version is already very good). Indeed a pain in the ass to train this but happy with the outcome.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.


Feel free to support us at:
https://www.patreon.com/user?u=90661954

Thank you all!.

David.

items.name: Lunar Radiance (月光Mix)
items.description:
Dream... not of what you are, but of what you want to be.

A mix targeted at enhancing lighting effects. The base checkpoint is also CLIP expanded using the (now deleted) checkpoint ALunarDreamV2. Primarily it is good at achieve dynamism in lighting effects. It is not a very bright checkpoint by default, but it is extremely good at doing backlighting, bokeh, caustics, and glare. It ends up very strong in twilight or sunset scenes. In addition, because of the clip expansion, you can use artists trained by ALunarDream to alter the style of the model organically without having use LoRAs. A comparison grid has been uploaded as an example.

One thing you might want to be aware of is that the light diffusion tends to sometimes express itself as mist or other radiance effects around a backlit object or character. I've bundled it with blessed-vae which is specifically good at picking up on noise offset by default so the pictures that come out will end up pretty dark. If you're not a fan of that, you can use any other VAE. I recommend Waifu Diffusion's for bright pastel colors and clearvae for in-between.

HuggingFace: https://huggingface.co/Jemnite/ALunarLight

My recommendation is to use the negative embeds for AuroraONE as they are the best at fixing your image while not changing the style IMO. If you notice, all of the images are generated with 

(worst quality, low quality:1.4), AuroraNegative, KHFB, negative_hands

With AuroraNegative and KHFB being AuroraONE's negative embeddings and negative_hands being this one.

items.name: BB95 AssMix (Furry Model)
items.description:
This is just BB95 Furry Mix with better buttholes.

All I have done is merge BB95 with a gaping/large insertion model as per the instructions here.

All credit goes to Bumblebee95 for the excellent BB95 Furry Mix. Please look at their model and give any support to them.

For instructions on use, anything on the BB95 page is right and should apply to this model too. Personally I prefer to use DDIM at 512*704 with 1.5 Hires Fix by Latent (nearest). Around 7.5-9 CFG scale works well, 0.6-0.7 denoising and I usually use around 30-80 steps (clip skip 1).

Images are the same seed with the same settings made on BB95v8.0 then BB95v8.0 AssMix. BB95v8.0 are on the left and BB95v8.0 AssMix are on the right. Some are quite similar and some results are very different but I think all have better buttholes in this model, if you're the same kind of degenerate as I am.

I strongly recommend using e621 tags and looking up images on e621 to see what the correct tags are (e.g., 'scut tail' instead of 'deer tail') as they will work much better, gelbooru tags may also work because of the merged model.
